";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45949:\"<section data-layout=\"article\" class=\"bg-white\">\r\n    <div class=\"container  py-rg\">\r\n        <div class=\"grid  gap-sm  grid-cols-1  sm:grid-cols-2  md:grid-cols-3  lg:grid-cols-4  xl:grid-cols-5  relative\">\r\n            \r\n            <!-- 1st column -->\r\n            <div class=\"hidden  xl:block  xl:col-end-s1\"></div>\r\n\r\n            <!-- Main collumn -->\r\n            <div class=\"col-end-s1  sm:col-end-s2  lg:col-end-s3\">\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"toc-start\"></div>\r\n\r\n                <div class=\"wysiwyg\">\r\n\r\n                    \n<h2>New free and premium features &#8211; speed up content delivery and identify slow plugins</h2>\n<p>WP-Optimize version 3.7.0 includes two new exciting optimisation features.</p>\n<p>In the free version, you can now automatically preload your content when a page or post is purged or updated. This ensures that your new content is instantly available to visitors, eliminating any potential delays.</p>\n<p>If you’re a premium user, you can now identify plugins which cause your site to slow down. With the table usage feature, you have the power to detect plugins which cause slow database queries, giving you the opportunity to replace them with faster alternatives.</p>\n<h3>Automatic preload feature (free)</h3>\n<p>Existing users can enable automatic cache preloading in their settings. This is enabled by default for new users.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to WP-Optimize &gt;&gt; Page cache &gt;&gt; Purge the cache.</li>\n<li>Tick the Automatically preload content after it is purged checkbox.</li>\n<li>Click the Save changes button.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<!-- image -->\r\n<figure data-layout=\"image\" class=\"overflow-hidden  rounded-md\" data-alt=\"Click \'Purge Cache\' button and select the checkbox for \'Automatically preload content after it is purged\'\">\r\n    <img decoding=\"async\"\r\n                class=\"bg-main-1/3  border  border-main-1/10\"\r\n                loading=\"lazy\"\r\n        alt=\"Click \'Purge Cache\' button and select the checkbox for \'Automatically preload content after it is purged\'\"\r\n        width=\"2048\"\r\n        height=\"798\"\r\n        src=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-640x249.webp\"\r\n        srcset=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-640x249.webp 640w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-1024x399.webp 1024w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-1440x561.webp 1440w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-300x117.webp 300w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-1280x499.webp 1280w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-768x299.webp 768w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-1680x655.webp 1680w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-1920x748.webp 1920w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize-600x234.webp 600w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/automatic-preload-feature-wp-optimize.webp 2048w\"\r\n        sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\r\n    >\r\n    </figure>\r\n<!-- image -->\n\n<h3>Identify slow plugins feature (exclusive to premium users)</h3>\n<p>To identify slow plugins:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Go to <strong>WP-Optimize &gt;&gt; Database &gt;&gt; Table usage.</strong></li>\n<li>Click the<strong> Run the query analysis for all executed queries in this site.</strong></li>\n<li>Select a plugin in <strong>Tables Usage Report</strong> to view detailed performance information.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<!-- image -->\r\n<figure data-layout=\"image\" class=\"overflow-hidden  rounded-md\" data-alt=\"In \'Tables usage\' tab, run the query analysis, then select the plugin from the \'Tables Usage Report\' dropdown\">\r\n    <img decoding=\"async\"\r\n                class=\"bg-main-1/3  border  border-main-1/10\"\r\n                loading=\"lazy\"\r\n        alt=\"In \'Tables usage\' tab, run the query analysis, then select the plugin from the \'Tables Usage Report\' dropdown\"\r\n        width=\"2048\"\r\n        height=\"1148\"\r\n        src=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-640x359.webp\"\r\n        srcset=\"https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-640x359.webp 640w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-1024x574.webp 1024w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-1440x807.webp 1440w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-300x168.webp 300w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-1280x718.webp 1280w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-768x431.webp 768w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-1680x942.webp 1680w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-1920x1076.webp 1920w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize-600x336.webp 600w, https://teamupdraft.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/identify-slow-plugins-feature-wp-optimize.webp 2048w\"\r\n        sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px\"\r\n    >\r\n    </figure>\r\n<!-- image -->\n\n<h3>Other improvements</h3>\n<p>We’ve fixed an issue with the cache scheduling feature which prevented it functioning properly due the user ID not being set when preloading via CRON.<br />\nWe’ve also fixed an inconsistency with the <code>smush_manager_send_command</code> function.</p>\n<p>For a full list of changes, please review the changelog below.</p>\n<h2>Changelog:</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Feature:</strong> Added an option to automatically preload URLs immediately after cache content is purged.</li>\n<li><strong>Feature:</strong> Premium &#8211; Gather data about table usage by filtering query event.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Cache &#8211; Scheduled preloading wasn&#8217;t working.</li>\n<li><strong>Fix:</strong> Inconsistency in <code>smush_manager_send_command</code> function.</li>\n<li><strong>REFACTOR:</strong> Smush &#8211; Popup styles, remove unused code.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Fix fatal implode error when updating to v3.5.0.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Image compression &#8211; Issue with cancelling smush image compression.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Improve module minification logic.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Premium &#8211; Unused images &#8211; Fixed popup when moving images to or restoring images from the trash.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Premium &#8211; Unused images &#8211; Placeholder images in unused images section.</li>\n<li><strong>Tweak:</strong> Added <code>security.md</code> file with information to report security issues.</li>\n</ul>\n\r\n\r\n                </div>\r\n\r\n                <!-- Author -->\r\n                <div class=\"mt-rg\">\r\n                    <h3 class=\"mb-xs\">About the author</h3>\r\n                    <div class=\"col-end-s5  flex\">\r\n                        <div>\r\n                            <div class=\"block  bg-white  border-3  border-orange  mr-xs  overflow-hidden  rounded-full  relative  size-[70px]\">\r\n                         